Setup

library(rstan)
options(mc.cores = parallel::detectCores())
rstan_options(auto_write = TRUE)
library(broom)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(bayesplot)
library(gridExtra)
plot_estimates <- function(fit, stan_data) {
    tidy(fit, pars = "theta", conf.int = TRUE) %>%
        bind_cols(naive = tapply(
            stan_data$y, stan_data$grp, function(x) mean(log(x)))) %>%
        ggplot(aes(estimate, term)) +
        geom_linerange(
            aes(xmin = conf.low, xmax = conf.high), colour = "orange", size = 3) +
        geom_point(shape = 21, size = 2.5, fill = "white") +
        geom_point(aes(naive, term), shape = 21, size = 4) +
        geom_vline(
            xintercept = mean(tapply(
                stan_data$y, stan_data$grp, function(x) mean(log(x)))),
            linetype = 3) +
        theme_minimal()
}

Data

# Data
N <- c(5, 10, 20)
mu <- c(1, 5, 2.7)
set.seed(2020)
grp <- rep(seq_along(N), times = N)
y <- unlist(Map(function(n, meanlog) rlnorm(n, meanlog), N, mu))
stan_data <- list(N = sum(N), J = length(N), y = y, grp = grp)

Models

Centred-parametrisation

\[ \begin{aligned} y_i &\sim \textrm{LogNormal}(\theta_{j[i]}, \sigma^2)\,,\\ \theta_j &\sim \textrm{Normal}(\mu_\theta, \sigma_\theta^2) \end{aligned} \] with priors \[ \begin{aligned} \sigma &\sim \textrm{Cauchy}(0, 2.5)\,,\\ \mu_\theta &\sim \textrm{Normal}(\text{mean}(\log{y}), 5)\,,\\ \sigma_\theta &\sim \textrm{Cauchy}(0, 2.5)\,. \end{aligned} \]

Model fit

mod1 <- stan_model("cp_lognormal.stan")
fit1 <- sampling(object = mod1, data = stan_data, iter = 4000, seed = 2020)

Parameter estimates

plot_estimates(fit1, stan_data)

Non-centred parametrisation

\[ \begin{aligned} y_i &\sim \textrm{LogNormal}(\theta_{j[i]}, \sigma^2)\,,\\ \theta_{\text{raw}, j} &\sim \textrm{Normal}(0, 1)\\ \theta_j &= \mu_\theta + \sigma_\theta \theta_{\text{raw}, j} \end{aligned} \] with priors \[ \begin{aligned} \sigma &\sim \textrm{Cauchy}(0, 2.5)\,,\\ \mu_\theta &\sim \textrm{Normal}(\text{mean}(\log{y}), 5)\,,\\ \sigma_\theta &\sim \textrm{Cauchy}(0, 2.5)\,. \end{aligned} \]

Model fit

Diagnostic

We use bayesplot to explore results.

color_scheme_set("darkgray")
theme_set(theme_minimal())

posterior1 <- as.array(fit1)
posterior2 <- as.array(fit2)
lp1 <- log_posterior(fit1)
lp2 <- log_posterior(fit2)
np1 <- nuts_params(fit1)
np2 <- nuts_params(fit2)
gg1 <- mcmc_parcoord(
    posterior1, 
    pars = c("theta[1]", "theta[2]", "theta[3]", "mu_theta", "sigma_theta"),
    np = np1)
gg2 <- mcmc_parcoord(
    posterior2, 
    pars = c("theta[1]", "theta[2]", "theta[3]", "mu_theta", "sigma_theta"),
    np = np2)
grid.arrange(gg1, gg2)

mcmc_pairs(
    posterior1,
    pars = c("theta[1]", "theta[2]", "theta[3]", "mu_theta", "sigma_theta"),
    np = np1,
    off_diag_args = list(size = 0.75))

mcmc_pairs(
    posterior2,
    pars = c("theta[1]", "theta[2]", "theta[3]", "mu_theta", "sigma_theta"),
    np = np2,
    off_diag_args = list(size = 0.75))
